reviews.review:
Pros:
1) Hooters restaurant food inside the hotel is very good.  It's better tasting than Hooters of Santa Monica;
2) I spotted a few hooter girls who range cute to gorgeous (eye-candy) from a male point-of-view;
3) Front desk staff are friendly;
4) Nice view from the window overlooking McCarran airport and the city at nighttime;
5) Plenty of souvenir stores inside.

Cons:
1) Guest parking is terrible.  Sometimes pack at night;
2) The guest room is your basic standard and low quality.  In fact, there's no refrigerator;
3) Don't recommend taking your kids in the casino area due to heavy smell of cigarette smoking and risk of exposure to second hand smoking;
4) The weather in the summertime is too hot.
5) The restaurant prices at the Mad Onion is at least $12 and up.  It's a bit cheaper dining at the Hooter restaurant.
